+{"id":"frankenjax-drbz","title":"Make BufferView slicing reject overflowing ranges","description":"Skill: /multi-pass-bug-hunting\n\nVerified issue: crates/fj-runtime/src/buffer.rs BufferView::slice currently computes offset + len before checking bounds. For inputs such as offset = usize::MAX and len = 1, debug builds panic on arithmetic overflow and optimized builds can wrap before reaching the slice range, violating the documented contract that out-of-bounds ranges return None.\n\nReproduction: call BufferView::from_buffer(&Buffer::new(vec![1, 2, 3], DeviceId(0))).slice(usize::MAX, 1). The current implementation panics instead of returning None.\n\nExpected fix: use checked_add for the end offset, return None on overflow, and keep existing valid/boundary slice behavior unchanged. Add a unit test covering the overflow case.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-28T20:28:58.475942648Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-28T20:29:01.810278837Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
