 {"id":"frankenjax-xfi","title":"UBS: clean FFI byte-conversion unwrap inventory","description":"Follow-up from frankenjax-gn6. UBS reports 28 try_into().unwrap()/expect() warnings, with sampled hits in fj-ffi tests and conformance FFI oracle byte conversions (for example crates/fj-ffi/src/call.rs and crates/fj-conformance/tests/ffi_oracle.rs). Introduce checked test helpers for fixed-width result byte decoding and replace direct try_into unwraps so conversion assumptions are explicit and failures carry context.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-27T05:48:22.893924794Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-27T05:56:51.637211690Z","closed_at":"2026-04-27T05:56:51.635282896Z","close_reason":"Completed checked fixed-byte FFI result decoding helpers and removed direct try_into unwrap byte conversions.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"frankenjax-xjpu","title":"Harden BufferView slice range overflow","description":"Multi-pass bug hunt found crates/fj-runtime/src/buffer.rs BufferView::slice computes offset + len before validating bounds. For adversarial or saturated usize inputs this can panic in debug builds due integer overflow, and in optimized builds can wrap before the subsequent slice expression panics or misclassifies the range. Replace the addition with checked_add so out-of-range or overflowing slices return None as documented. Add a regression test using usize::MAX to prove BufferView::slice is panic-free and returns None for overflowing ranges. Validate with rch cargo test -p fj-runtime, rch cargo check -p fj-runtime --all-targets, rch cargo clippy -p fj-runtime --all-targets -- -D warnings, cargo fmt --check, and ubs on the touched file.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-28T20:28:47.354876805Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-28T20:28:47.584388428Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
